{# TITLE: Common Questions #}{# KEYWORDS: Hand #}<p><b>What Is Plastic Surgery?</b></p>
<p>Plastic Surgery derives its name from the Greek word &quot;plastikos&quot; which means to remodel or restore. Plastic Surgery at Summit Medical Group encompasses the fields of cosmetic, reconstructive, and hand surgery.</p>
<p><b>How Do I Choose A Plastic Surgeon?</b></p>
<p>Any doctor may refer to himself and advertise as a &quot;Cosmetic Surgeon&quot; regardless of his training. Only qualified surgeons who have completed a residency in Plastic Surgery and have passed examinations given by the American Board of Plastic Surgery are board certified in Plastic Surgery. Certification by the American Board of Plastic Surgery is an indication that the doctor has completed extensive training and is qualified to perform your plastic surgery operation.</p>
<p><b>Who Is An Ideal Candidate?</b></p>
<p>Anyone seeking to improve their appearance and also are realistic about what cosmetic plastic surgery can accomplish.</p>
<p><b>Can I Afford Plastic Surgery?</b></p>
<p>We understand cosmetic surgery can be costly, but there are a number of ways to finance these expenses. Our staff would be happy to review the options with you at any time.</p>